=== Tinnitus
<subsec:tinnitus>

*Clinical Presentation.*

    - Ringing, buzzing, hissing, or roaring sounds
    - Unilateral or bilateral
    - Constant or intermittent
    - Volume may fluctuate with fatigue, stress, or exertion
    - Can be severely disabling and interfere with sleep

*Mechanism.*
Tinnitus may reflect cochlear damage (high metabolic demands make cochlear hair cells vulnerable), auditory nerve dysfunction, or central auditory processing abnormalities.
